The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 May is 276,271 (31,841.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 May, there were 866 new confirmed cases (99.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 May, there were 958 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (92 fewer cases).
